track_notes: A good route if you are travelling light, but there are easier ways up - G4YSS uses one from further north - starts around Causeway I believe. Most people visit from Tor Dike, and combine the activation with one of Great Whernside. Try this route though if you wish to go to and from the pub at Cray  but dont carry two large slabs as I did, it was a killer!
track_title: Steep route up Buckden Pike from White Lion Inn Cray

track_notes: This follows the wall along the ridge.
track_title: From Cattle Grid at Little Hunters Sleets

track_notes: Small off road parking area at SD 9456 7995, Through gate at SD 9454 7999 into field.  Follow vehicle track across fields, then turn steeply up hill.  Continue on vehicle track, slightly less distinct, to gate at SD 9516 7927.  Then cross country (no path) for a short way to join the bridle way and follow to the summit.
track_title: From small parking area on Minor road

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 3h 5m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
